Armstrong Bakam Bauchi State Governor, Bala Mohammed, has awarded the construction of a 58.4-kilometre road at the cost of N8bn. The road, linking the Alkaleri and Tafawa Balewa local government areas of the state, has Yalwan Duguri, Badaran Dutse and others as beneficiary communities. Inaugurating the road construction at Burga, Tafawa Balewa Local Government Area, the governor said over N4bn had already been released for the work. Mohammed said the gesture was in line with his administrationâ€™s policy of providing infrastructure and improving the welfare of the people in the state. He said adequate attention would be given to facilitate the timely completion of the project. Earlier in his speech, the Permanent Secretary, Ministry of Works and Transport, Mr Stephen Abubakar, said when the road was completed, it would increase socioeconomic opportunities for the beneficiary communities. He explained that the road was designed to have a length of 58.4km, with a total width of 10.3m, comprising a carriageway of 7.3m and 1.5m shoulders on each side. Abubakar said the road would have four bridges, 45 box culverts and 70 pipe culverts of different sizes. He added the project would be completed within 24 months. Speaking on behalf of the beneficiary communities, the Caretaker Committee Chairman, Tafawa Balewa Local Government Area, Mr Kefas Magaji, commended the governor for the gesture. Copyright PUNCH.
